Botswanaâ€™s trade deficit narrowed to
1.2 billion pula in the third quarter from 1.5 billion pula in
the previous three months as diamond exports increased, the
statistics office said.  Exports rose 12 percent to 8.2 billion pula, while imports
gained 6.9 percent to 9.5 billion pula, the Central Statistics
Office, based in the capital, Gaborone, said in a report on its
website today. Diamond exports, which accounted for 76 percent
of all shipments, increased 4.3 percent to 5.2 billion pula in
